Why $99 for Pro:
- DojoChamp charges $99 and has less — no multi-location, no website builder, no WordPress plugin
- At $49 you're signaling you're a budget product, which makes sales harder not easier
- $99 is still 75% cheaper than Mindbody — "Mindbody alternative" SEO and ads become very compelling

Why $179 for Academy/multi-location:
- Gymdesk charges $150–200 and that's their main differentiator — match it
- Multi-location customers have higher willingness to pay (they're running a real business)
- You can always negotiate for large chains

One thing to decide: Do you raise prices for existing customers or grandfather them? I'd grandfather analty matters more than the delta — and move new signups to the new pricing immediately whenmulti-location ships.

The headline pitch writes itself: "Everything DojoChamp does, plus multi-location and a native app, for the same price."
